President Obama has nominated Judge Charles Bernard Day and Kathleen M. Williams to United States District Court judgeships. Judge Charles Bernard Day has served as a United States Magistrate Judge for the District of Maryland for 13 years. He began his legal career as an Assistant State's Attorney for Montgomery County in 1985 and worked as a civil litigation attorney before his appointment to the court in 1997. Judge Day received his J.D. from the University of Maryland School of Law. Kathleen M. Williams has served as the Federal Public Defender for the Southern District of Florida since 1995. She has also worked as an associate in private practice and as an Assistant United States Attorney. Ms. Williams received her J.D. from the University of Miami School of Law. Both nominees have been recognized for their distinguished records of service and commitment to justice.